manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: NATURELO has a unique approach to formulating our supplements — we always use the cleanest most bioavailable ingredients whenever possible so that you can get the most benefit from each supplement. We seek out plant-based nutrients which means sourcing vitamin E from sunflowers (instead of synthetics), Vitamin D from lichen (instead of animal based lanolin which comes from sheep grease!) and Calcium from marine algae (instead of cheaper calcium carbonate which is actually made from rocks!) If that isn’t enough, we also boost our supplements with proprietary blends of organic fruits, vegetables and botanicals for an extra source of real whole food nutrition. Like organic broccoli, carrots, blueberries, kale, spinach, heart healthy turmeric, immune boosting mushrooms… we could go on and on and on.... Naturelo... from Nature with Love

Natural Immune Support Show your immune system some extra love with a little help from nature. Our Immune Support Blend includes the power of elderberry, a tiny superfruit with a mighty reputation for supporting immune and respiratory health. Our Whole Food Multivitamin includes a blend of real, organic fruits and vegetables for an extra boost of whole food nutrition. It’s got a colorful spectrum of nature’s goodness, including beets, carrots, blueberries, spinach, pomegranate, and kale. Not only are the fruits and veggies organic, our multivitamins are completely non-GMO and vegan, with no preservatives added.

reviews.reviewText: great product, no taste, no odor and has what I need. I contacted Naturelo company regarding the change in color of contents of capsules which appears to be a concern to other customers and got an answer almost immediately and here it is:"Due to the variations in the soil, the sort of the plant, the climate, the season it was harvested, etc., there is a difference in the taste, smell and color.. This variation is normal and happens with every new batch of multivitamins we make. We do not use dyes, scents, fillers or binders"So feel confident that you didn't get a batch of bad supplements.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Satisfies My Checklist But Expensive
reviews.reviewText: It has been surprisingly difficult to find a supplement that satisfies these requirements:1. Suitable for vegans, vegetarians and pescatarians.2. Contains the right amounts of Vitamin B12, Vitamin D3, Iodine and Zinc recommended for those on a largely plant-based diet.3. Not too much Vitamin A.4. Vitamin A in the form of Natural Beta Carotene.5. Not too much Vitamin E.6. Contains Vitamin K2.7. No overly high amounts of any particular nutrient.8. No iron because I am no longer menstruating.This product satisfies my checklist but I'm still looking for something that is less expensive.
